<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>For GWs comments on the Greenland winter at Mount Vernon, see his diary entries for late January and early February 1772.</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-09-02-pb-0019">[19]</span>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For some of the accounts relating to John Parke Custiss expenditures at Annapolis, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0004&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0004-fn-0003#GEWN-02-09-02-0004-fn-0003" class="document">Boucher to GW, 15 Jan., nn.3</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0004&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0004-fn-0006#GEWN-02-09-02-0004-fn-0006" class="document">6</a>. This and what follows is clearly Bouchers response to a missing letter from GW written after his receiving Bouchers letter of 15 January.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Frazier charged board at the rate of 35 per year for John Parke Custis, and at 25 for his servant. For Joshua Fraziers bill for boarding young Custis, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0282&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0282-fn-0004#GEWN-02-08-02-0282-fn-0004" class="document">Boucher to GW, 18 Dec. 1770, n.4</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0004" class="document">15 Jan. 1772</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0014&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0002#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0002" class="document">note 2</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0004&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0004-fn-0001#GEWN-02-09-02-0004-fn-0001" class="document">Boucher to GW, 15 Jan. 1772, n.1</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0016" class="document">Boucher to GW, 5 March</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0007-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0007">7</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0014&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0002#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0002" class="document">note 2</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0008-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0014-fn-0008">8</a>

